- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of randomized algorithms for approximating polytope volume. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper deals with numerical methods for approximating polytope volume. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with polytopes, which are objects studied in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the runtime of the implemented algorithms and their dependence on various parameters.
